An Algerian military transport plane crashed on Wednesday near the capital, state news agency APS said, with reports of around 100 soldiers on board. There was no immediate word on casualties after the plane went down near an airbase soon after taking off. Algerian television showed images of the burning wreckage. The aircraft is an Ilyushin II-76, which is capable of carrying around 120 passengers, according to the source, who did not want to be named.  More follows...   There has been a sharp drop in the number of students qualified to study for degrees.